# input_alias_surface.numos — Phase 9A input-parity regression guard (golden-free).
#
# Purpose: prove that the WHOLE .numos script-token vocabulary still PARSES and
# DISPATCHES. loadScript() validates every `key NAME` up front and exits 2 on the
# first unknown token (scriptNameToKeyCode -> KeyCode::NONE, NativeHal.cpp:1306-1307),
# so if any alias is ever renamed/removed/misspelled this script fails at LOAD before
# running a single frame. It is the canary for the alias map edited in this phase.
#
# This script makes NO golden claim, takes NO screenshot, and opens NO app. It runs
# entirely at the LAUNCHER (MENU mode). None of the tokens below map to an LVGL
# navigation key (no up/down/left/right/enter), so in the MENU branch each is pushed
# into LvglKeypad with no LV_KEY mapping (LvglKeypad.cpp:48-53) and is a harmless
# no-op: focus never moves and no app launches. The final `assert_app Menu` therefore
# holds and emits the "PASS - " marker the CI input-parity step greps for.
#
# Coverage = every spelled alias group in scriptNameToKeyCode (NativeHal.cpp:384):
#   * Phase 9A additions:   logbase, log_n (-> LOG_BASE), zoom (-> ZOOM)
#   * Phase 8B aliases:     exe, table, f1..f5, preans
#   * app/var/const tokens: ans, graph, sto, sqrt, sin, cos, tan, ln, log, pi, e,
#                           neg, negate, frac, dot, sd, freeeq, shift, alpha
# (Symbols + - * / ^ . ( ) = and bare digits are exercised by the calc_* suite.)
#
# NOTE: `key exe`, `key table`, `key f1..f5`, `key graph`, `key zoom`, `key logbase`
# resolve to REAL existing KeyCodes; whether a given APP acts on them is app logic and
# out of scope here — this test only asserts the emulator can NAME and DISPATCH them.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/input_alias_surface.numos \
#           --frames 400 --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error (an alias went missing) · 4 assertion failure.

log "input_alias_surface: validating script-alias parse + dispatch at launcher"
wait 200

# Phase 9A additions (must resolve to LOG_BASE / ZOOM — existing KeyCodes).
key logbase
key log_n
key zoom

# Phase 8B + app/var/const alias surface (all map to existing KeyCodes).
key ans
key preans
key exe
key table
key graph
key f1
key f2
key f3
key f4
key f5
key sto
key shift
key alpha
key sqrt
key sin
key cos
key tan
key ln
key log
key pi
key e
key neg
key negate
key frac
key dot
key sd
key freeeq
wait 20

# Still at the launcher: no token above is an LVGL nav key, so nothing launched.
assert_app Menu
log "input_alias_surface: PASS - all alias tokens parsed and dispatched (still at Menu)"
